text.tspan: Macroplastics in the surface ocean, 1950 to 2050
Macroplastics are buoyant plastic materials greater 0.5 centimeters in diameter. Future global accumulation in the surface ocean is shown
under three plastic emissions scenarios: (1) emissions to the oceans stop in 2020; (2) they stagnate at 2020 emission rates; or (3) continue to
grow until 2050 in line with historical plastic production rates.
Data source: Lebreton et al. (2019). A global mass budget for positively buoyant macroplastic debris in the ocean.
